{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease a metal baking tin that fits in the Varoma without obstructing all holes (e.g. Bundt cake tin, Ø 20 cm top and Ø 12 cm bottom, or loaf tin 21 cm x 10 cm x 6 cm), dust with semolina and set aside.","Place sugar and 5 g lemon zest (from approx. half a lemon) in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>30 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter, eggs, milk, 20 g lemon juice, flour, baking powder and salt and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to prepared tin and cover tin with heat-resistant cling film. Clean mixing bowl.","Place water in mixing bowl and set Varoma dish in position. Place baking tin in Varoma dish, close Varoma and steam <nobr>70 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, to prepare glaze, place chocolate and oil in a heat-resistant freezer bag, seal tightly and set aside.","Remove Varoma and place bag containing chocolate mixture in Varoma dish, next to baking tin, making sure some holes remain unobstructed. Set Varoma back in position and steam a further <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Set Varoma aside, remove baking tin and bag with melted chocolate and set aside. After 5 minutes, remove cling film and allow cake to cool for 30 minutes in tin.","Transfer cake from tin to wire rack. Mix chocolate glaze by kneading it carefully, snip a corner off the bag and pour glaze evenly over cake. Slice and serve warm or at room temperature."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["150 g unsalted butter, cut in pieces, plus extra for greasing","2 Tbsp semolina, for dusting","180 g sugar","5 g lemon zest (approx. half lemon)","3 eggs","20 g milk","20 g lemon juice","180 g plain flour","1 ½ tsp baking powder","1 pinch salt","1400 g water","100 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa solids), cut in pieces","1 tsp neutral oil (e.g. sunflower, groundnut)"]}],"id":"r150940","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-xe3JhmviUAE\/XZWrVo__JGI\/AAAAAAAAfl4\/oFI3uEN65AEWK_jseH